ce:section.ce:para:
In this work, the sensing mechanism has been proved by the XPS spectra (Fig. 1
                        ), visualization results (Fig. 2
                        ) and FLT results (Fig. 3
                        ). Briefly, the detection of Hg2+ occurs via the static fluorescence quenching (turn-off) of SCDs, which is mainly caused by the electron transfer effect between the SCDs and Hg2+. The addition of TM into the SCDs/Hg2+ system enabled the formation of TM-Hg complexes, which stopped the electron transfer reactions between the SCDs and Hg2+, thereby caused the static fluorescence enhancement (turn-on) of SCDs.
